SIMPLE: ose
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -ose
<hw>-ose</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>suff.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>-osus</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>-ose</ets>. Cf. <er>-ous</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A suffix denoting <xex>full of</xex>,
<xex>containing</xex>, <xex>having the qualities of</xex>,
<xex>like</xex>; as in verb<xex>ose</xex>, full of words;
pil<xex>ose</xex>, hairy; glob<xex>ose</xex>, like a globe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A suffix indicating that the
substance to the name of which it is affixed is <sig>a member of the
carbohydrate group</sig>; <as>as in cellul<ex>ose</ex>,
sucr<ex>ose</ex>, dextr<ex>ose</ex>, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osier</ent>⟦br⟧
